I use the default java.lang.RuntimeException, my RuntimeException subclass do not redefined the equals method. 
For example, this two simple test passed :

    @Test
    public void test() {
        assertThat(new RuntimeException("A first message"))
                .isEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively(new RuntimeException("A second message"));
    }

    @Test
    public void test2() {
        assertThat(new RuntimeException("A first message"))
                .isEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively("A second message");
    }

It seems to ignore the RuntimeException.

I have a fix but in addition to compare `Exception` messages, it also compares their stack traces which will likely never be equals.
```java
@Test
public void should_report_exception_message_difference() {
    // GIVEN
    RuntimeException exception1 = new RuntimeException("message1");
    RuntimeException exception2 = new RuntimeException("message2");
    // THEN
    assertThat(exception1).isEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively(exception2);
}
```
reports the following error on the message and stack trace fields:
```
java.lang.AssertionError: 
Expecting:
  <java.lang.RuntimeException: message1>
to be equal to:
  <java.lang.RuntimeException: message2>
when recursively comparing field by field, but found the following difference(s):

Path to difference: <stackTrace>
- actual  : <org.assertj.core.internal.objects.Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.should_report_exception_message_difference(Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.java:474)>
- expected: <org.assertj.core.internal.objects.Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.should_report_exception_message_difference(Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.java:475)>

Path to difference: <detailMessage>
- actual  : <"message1">
- expected: <"message2">

... full error stack trace omitted for brevity.
```
If I set the same message the stack trace fields will still differ:
```
  @Test
  public void should_report_exception_message_difference() {
    // GIVEN
    RuntimeException exception1 = new RuntimeException("message1");
    RuntimeException exception2 = new RuntimeException("message1");
    // THEN
    assertThat(exception1).isEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursively(exception2);
  }
```
fails with:
```
java.lang.AssertionError: 
Expecting:
  <java.lang.RuntimeException: message1>
to be equal to:
  <java.lang.RuntimeException: message1>
when recursively comparing field by field, but found the following difference(s):

Path to difference: <stackTrace>
- actual  : <org.assertj.core.internal.objects.Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.should_report_exception_message_difference(Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.java:474)>
- expected: <org.assertj.core.internal.objects.Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.should_report_exception_message_difference(Objects_assertIsEqualToComparingFieldByFieldRecursive_Test.java:475)>

... full error stack trace omitted for brevity.
```

@agauchy is that behavior what you expect ?

It is not yet possible to ignore fields in recursive comparison but you can register a comparator for `Exception` (that would compare their message for example).

